making changes in git process : 
1) create a repo
https://help.github.com/articles/generating-ssh-keys

2) 
=> Create a new repository on the command line

touch README.md
git init
git add README.md
git commit -m "first commit"
git remote add origin https://github.com/richil-bhalerao/doccapp.git
git push -u origin master
(Before this step u might need to add ssh keys => https://help.github.com/articles/generating-ssh-keys)
or
(git remote set-url origin https://richil-bhalerao@github.com/richil-bhalerao/doccapp.git)


=> Push an existing repository from the command line

git remote add origin https://github.com/richil-bhalerao/doccapp.git
git push -u origin master


=> 
    Make your change.
   1. git add - this stages your changes for committing
   2. git commit - this commits your staged changes locally
   3. git push - this pushes your committed changes to a remote



